import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all capital cities?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    capital_cities = data.groupby('state')['city'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
    capital_cities.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of capital cities?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=capital_cities.max(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend([f'Maximum number of capital cities: {capital_cities.max()}'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['lon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Longitude: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axhline(y=data['lat'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Latitude: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    states = data['state'].unique()
    colors = plt.cm.tab20.colors[:len(states)]
    for i, state in enumerate(states):
        state_data = data[data['state'] == state]
        ax.scatter(state_data['lon'], state_data['lat'], color=colors[i], label=state)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude within each state?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
